id: pm-59gj
title: Build package-first pm ecosystem and install command
description: "Build a package-first pm ecosystem around installable project-management packages while using Pi/OpenClaw only as architecture references for npm/git/local package sourcing, manifest contracts, diagnostics, and small-core extensibility."
type: Feature
status: open
priority: 0
tags[6]: extensions,install,packages,pi,pm-cli,sdk
created_at: "2026-05-11T17:39:33.123Z"
updated_at: "2026-05-24T22:53:31.573Z"
author: codex-agent
acceptance_criteria: External package architecture research is documented in tracker; pm package/install plan is decomposed into child work; pm install supports managed package sources while preserving extension compatibility; SDK/docs/tests stay provider-neutral and pm-specific; full CLI/SDK dogfood passes in a temporary project; telemetry and Sentry verification are recorded.
parent: pm-rnpb
