body: "Package-first architecture plan after external package-manager references:\\n\\n1. Keep bare pm core limited to project-management primitives: item storage/format, history, locking, settings, output, command runtime, lifecycle commands, SDK contracts, package loading, governance, and minimal health.\\n2. Treat workflow-specific behavior as optional packages unless it is required to manage pm items without packages. First delivered slice: pm-hxp2 extracted Beads/Todos import/export bridges into installable first-party package roots.\\n3. Keep follow-up package work provider-neutral and pm-specific: pm-t5ud for manifest/package contract design, pm-su6i for pm package resource loading, pm-lwun for package-first docs/UX terminology, and pm-2b3l for package gallery metadata.\\n4. Later package-boundary candidates include templates, search providers/vector stores, calendar presentations, telemetry/Sentry adapters, and external bridge workflows after their core contracts are narrowed.\\n5. Verification protocol for each slice: sandboxed PM_PATH/PM_GLOBAL_PATH tests, temp-project pm install dogfood, contracts/health/package doctor, full coverage, observability checks, commit/push, and green GitHub Actions."
